manageSaleTypeBatch(uint256,uint256,uint.details: set {_saleType} to saleType of trees in range {_startTreeId} and {_endTreeId}

params._endTreeId: _ending tree id to set saleType value
params._startTreeId: starting tree id to set saleType value

returns._0: true if all trees saleType value successfully set and false otherwise

mintAssignedTree(uint256,address).details: mint a tree to funder and set saleType to 0

params._funder: address of funder to mint tree for

mintTree(uint256,address).details: mint a tree to funder of tree

params._funder: funder of a new tree sold in Regular
params._lastFundedTreeId: The last tree funded in the regular sale

returns._0: the last tree funded after update

mintTreeById(uint256,address).details: mint an already planted tree with id to funder

plantAssignedTree(uint256,string,uint64,.details: planter with permission to plant, can plant its assigned tree NOTE emited an {AssignedTreePlanted} event

plantTree(string,uint64,uint16).details: planter plant a tree NOTE emited a {TreePlanted} event

params._treeId: id of tree to reset saleType value

resetSaleTypeBatch(uint256,uint256,uint2.details: reset saleType of trees in range of {_startTreeId} and {_endTreeId} with saleType value of {_saleType}

params._endTreeId: ending tree id to reset saleType
params._startTreeId: starting tree id to reset saleType

setUpdateInterval(uint256).details: admin set the minimum time to send next update request NOTE emit an {TreeUpdateIntervalChanged} event

updateTree(uint256,string).details: planter of tree send update request for tree NOTE emited a {TreeUpdated} event

updateTreeSpecs(uint64,string).details: script role update treeSpecs NOTE emit a {TreeSpecsUpdated} event

params._treeId: id of tree to update treeSpecs

verifyAssignedTree(uint256,bool).details: admin or allowed verifier can verify or reject plant for assigned tree. NOTE emited an {AssignedTreeVerified} or {AssignedTreeRejected} event

params._isVerified: true for verify and false for reject

verifyTree(uint256,bool).details: admin or allowed verifier can verify or rejects the pending trees NOTE emited a {TreeVerified} or {TreeRejected} event

params._isVerified: true for verify and false for reject

verifyUpdate(uint256,bool).details: admin or allowed verifier can verifiy or reject update request for tree. NOTE based on the current time of verifing and plant date, age of tree calculated and set as the treeStatus NOTE if a token exist for that tree (minted before) planter of tree funded based on calculated tree status NOTE emited a {TreeUpdatedVerified} or {TreeUpdateRejected} event

params._isVerified: true for verify and false for reject
params._treeId: id of tree to verify update request

treeUpdateInterval.return: minimum time to send next update request

returns._0: minimum time to send next update request

isTreeFactory().notice: NOTE {isTreeFactory} set inside the initialize to {true}

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: return if the forwarder is trusted to forward relayed transactions to us. the forwarder is required to verify the sender's signature, and verify the call is not a replay.

tempTrees(uint256).notice: NOTE mapping of treeId to TempTree struct

treeUpdates(uint256).notice: NOTE mapping of treeId to TreeUpdate struct

trees(uint256).notice: NOTE mapping of treeId to TreeData Struct
